DMI-MD Implementation in LAMMPS
Developed by Jiseok Oh, Yoosang Son, and Hyungjun Kim
2026 M-Degign Lab @KAIST

# 1. Setting domain.cpp and domain.h
To export time-averaved ensemble charge density, grid.cpp should be used as a LAMMPS class.

We use grid class developed in earlier DFT-CES QM/MM mean field studies.
Our simulation is based on grid class in LAMMPS 11Aug17 version in https://github.com/SeungJay/DFT-CES/tree/main/DFT-CES_MD
which is directly imported as grid.cpp and grid.h

In domain.h, add these lines:

  class Grid *grid;
  void set_grid(int, char **); 

Also, in domain.cpp, add these lines in the constructor: 
 
  char **args2 = new char*[8];
  grid = NULL;
  args2[0] = (char *) "empty";
  args2[1] = (char *) "yes";
  args2[2] = (char *) "5";
  args2[3] = (char *) "empty";
  args2[4] = (char *) "empty";
  args2[5] = (char *) "empty";
  args2[6] = (char *) "empty";
  args2[7] = (char *) "empty";
  set_grid(8,args2);
  delete [] args2;

and in the destructor:
  
  delete grid;

domain.cpp should include grid.h
  
  #include "grid.h"


Or, grid class can be automatically patched by the patch file provided in the link. 
Compile LAMMPS with these files.

# 2. Grid Parsing and Cube Saving
Using the grid class provided, fix_cubesave stores accumulated charge density during the simulation, 
and grid.cpp time averages and saves the final rho.cube. 

For ordinary molecules and ions, fix arguments are fix_name group_ID cubesave supercell_factor cubeID (any string)

fix              h2oGrid h2o cubesave 81 1 h2ocube
fix              ionGrid ion cubesave 81 0 ioncube
grid             ./empty85.cube yes 2 ion.cube h2o.cube

For tip4p water molecules, fix arguments are fix_name group_ID cubesave supercell_factor cubeID tip4p typeO typeH theta blen qdist.
typeO/H are types of O/H atoms, theta is HOH angle in degrees, blen is the O-H bond length(in angstroms, probably), and qdist is O-M(massless site) length.

fix              ionGrid ion cubesave 81 0 ioncube   
fix              h2oGrid t4p cubesave 81 2 tip4p 2 1 104.52 0.975 0.156
grid             ./empty85.cube yes 2 ion.cube t4p.cube

When tip4p is specified, the location of M site is computed by cubesave.cpp

# 3. Running DMI-IMD simulation
DMI-IMD routine is implemented in LAMMPS via fix_dmiimd.cpp 

Datafile requirement:
- Atom ID arrangement: {real atoms} -> {slab atoms} -> {image atoms}
- ID(i, image) - ID(i, real) = N for all i 

LAMMPS input:
- fix argument: a_1, b_1, c_1, a_2, b_2, c_2, x_ag, y_ag, N(spacing), multiplier, numpermol
- fix argument for tip4p: a_1, b_1, c_1, a_2, b_2, c_2, x_ag, y_ag, N(spacing), multiplier, tip4p, typeO theta blen qdist.
- Top mirror c_1 - exp(a_1-b_1*z), Hollow mirror c_2 - exp(a_2 - b_2*z)
- Honeycomb hexagonal plane wave interpolation between two mirrors. 
- multiplier = -1.0 when interslab potential is directly fitted from binding curve. 
- multiplier = 0.0 for ions. 
- Exapmle input lines:

fix h2oimage h2os dmiimd 12.01085951 1.546811985 8.610247221 8.318773804 1.080549146 8.610247221 4.2285459840 4.395561901 11423 -1.0 3
fix h2oimage h2os dmiimd 12.01085951 1.546811985 8.610247221 8.318773804 1.080549146 8.610247221 4.2285459840 4.395561901 11423 -1.0 tip4p 2 104.52 0.975 0.156

- Example printouts in the output file of LAMMPS:

#### DMI-IMD: Simulation Information for group h2os ####
- Top mirror: -exp(12.010860 - 1.546812*z) + 8.610247 and Hollow mirror: -exp(8.318774 - 1.080549*z) + 8.610247
 - Force subtraction with group h2os weight -1.000000
####
#### DMI-IMD: Simulation Information for group ions ####
- Top mirror: -exp(12.010860 - 1.546812*z) + 8.610247 and Hollow mirror: -exp(8.318774 - 1.080549*z) + 8.610247
 - No force subtraction with group ions
####
#### DMI-IMD: Cubefile Saving Information ####
- supercell factor = 81
- cubefile ID      = 0
#### DMI-IMD: Cubefile Saving Information ####
- supercell factor = 81
- cubefile ID      = 1
#### DMI-IMD: Grid File Info ####
- Grid file has been parsed: ./empty85.cube
- # of atoms in grid: 16
- # of grid points: 72 80 1152
- grid spacing: 0.070494 0.073259 0.073785 Angs
grid will be saved in ion.cube
grid will be saved in h2o.cube


# 3. Analysis
edlanal2.py performs post-processing of LAMMPS trajectory code. MDAnalysis installation is required.
